# Project Constitution

## Principles

### I. Documentation-First Direction

Product direction starts in `docs/`. Specs, plans, tasks, and implementation must preserve documented
decisions or explicitly update them.

### II. Prototype Before Scalable UI

Navigable prototypes are requirement-discovery artifacts. They guide UX, data, and workflows, but
production implementation must follow the project architecture and quality bar.

### III. Spec Kit Traceability

Feature work should move through Spec Kit artifacts in `specs/` when scope is significant. Generated
artifacts must remain aligned with `README.md`, `docs/`, and this constitution.

### IV. Compatibility By Default

Prefer additive changes and established project patterns. Breaking API, schema, or workflow changes
require explicit approval.

### V. Documentation Closeout

Every implementation must update affected docs plus `docs/handoff.md`, `docs/roadmap.md`, and
`docs/next-spec-prompt.md` before it is reported complete.

## Governance

Changes to this constitution must explain why the process changed and what templates, rules, or skills
must be updated to stay aligned.

